<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-09-03T02:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-09-03T02:00:00-05:00" n="1410" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1410">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 867.4016/117</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Turkey</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_MH1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Morgenthau</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the</hi>
                            <gloss type="to">
                                <hi rend="italic">Secretary of State</hi>
                            </gloss>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Constantinople</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-09-03T09:00:00+02:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">September 3, 1915, 9 a. m.</hi>
                                </date>
                                <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received September 6, 9 a.
                                m.</hi>]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>1005. Minister of War has promised to permit departure of such Armenians
                            to the United States whose emigration I vouch for as <hi rend="italic">bona fide</hi>. Destruction of Armenian race in Turkey is
                            progressing rapidly. Massacre reported at Angora and Brusa. Will you
                            suggest to <persName>Cleveland Dodge</persName>, <persName>Charles
                                Crane</persName>, <persName>John R. Mott</persName>,
                                <persName>Stephen Wise</persName>, and others to form committee to
                            raise funds and provide means to save some of the Armenians and assist
                            the poorer ones to emigrate, and perhaps to enlist California, Oregon,
                            and Washington to transport some of these people direct to their shores
                            via Panama Canal?</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_MH1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Morgenthau</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>